{"selectedVerses":[{"reference":{"book":"Amos","chapter":7,"verse":17},"text":"Therefore Thus says the LORD: \u0022\u0027Your wife shall be a prostitute in the city, and your sons and your daughters shall fall by the sword, and your land shall be divided up with a measuring line; you yourself shall die in an unclean land, and Israel shall surely go into exile away from its land.\u0027\u0022"},{"reference":{"book":"Ezekiel","chapter":39,"verse":28},"text":"Then they shall know that I am the LORD their God, because I sent them into exile among the nations and then assembled them into their own land. I will leave none of them remaining among the nations anymore."},{"reference":{"book":"Jeremiah","chapter":29,"verse":7},"text":"But seek the welfare of the city where I have sent you into exile, and pray to the LORD on its behalf, for in its welfare you will find your welfare."},{"reference":{"book":"Amos","chapter":1,"verse":5},"text":"I will break the gate-bar of Damascus, and cut off the inhabitants from the Valley of Aven, and him who holds the scepter from Beth-eden; and the people of Syria shall go into exile to Kir,\u0022 says the LORD."},{"reference":{"book":"Ezekiel","chapter":33,"verse":21},"text":"In the twelfth year of our exile, in the tenth month, on the fifth day of the month, a fugitive from Jerusalem came to me and said, \u0022The city has been struck down.\u0022"}],"allVerseReferences":[{"book":"2 Samuel","chapter":15,"verse":19},{"book":"2 Kings","chapter":25,"verse":11},{"book":"1 Chronicles","chapter":6,"verse":15},{"book":"2 Kings","chapter":25,"verse":21},{"book":"2 Kings","chapter":25,"verse":27},{"book":"1 Chronicles","chapter":9,"verse":1},{"book":"1 Chronicles","chapter":5,"verse":6},{"book":"1 Chronicles","chapter":5,"verse":22},{"book":"1 Chronicles","chapter":5,"verse":26},{"book":"1 Chronicles","chapter":8,"verse":6},{"book":"2 Chronicles","chapter":36,"verse":20},{"book":"Ezra","chapter":6,"verse":21},{"book":"Nehemiah","chapter":1,"verse":